## Refresh Rules

| Trigger | Signal | Refresh Path |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| View appears | — | `.task` in ClubAnalyticsDashboardView |
| Period changed | — | `.onChange(of: period)` |
| Cancellation confirmed | `appState.lastCancellationCredit` | `.onChange` → reload |
| Confirmed booking created | `appState.lastConfirmedBookingClubID` | `.onChange` → reload (club-scoped) |
| Attendance upsert/delete | `appState.lastAttendanceUpdateClubID` | `.onChange` → reload (club-scoped) |
| App returns to foreground | `scenePhase == .active` | `.onChange(of: scenePhase)` → reload |
| Pull-to-refresh | — | Not wired — analytics has no `.refreshable` |

All refresh paths call `fetchClubAdvancedAnalytics(for:days:)` which is guard-gated to skip re-entrant calls (`loadingAnalyticsClubIDs`).

